      <hedline>
        <hl1>My Name Is Not Robert</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jeffrey Scott Beckerman letter on Benjamin Weiser's August 6 article on wrongful imprisonment of Kerry Sanders holds it is arrogant of psychiatrist to trivialize right of innocent to remain free (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I could forgive Dr. Chung's incorrect diagnosis of Kerry Sanders, as he appears to be an overworked civil servant. But the psychiatrist's comment that his wrongfully accused patient should thank New York State is an arrogant trivialization of the right of the innocent to remain free.</p>
        <p>Jeffrey Scott Beckerman  Short Hills, N.J.</p>
      </block>
